   TEXAS-SCHOOLS-BUSH (Brownsville, Texas) _ On national
examinations, Texan school children have begun to show up their
peers in other states. The trend has become so consistent that
Texas' public school system, long among the nation's most troubled,
is viewed today as an emerging model of equity, progress and
accountability. Texas children are the primary beneficiaries. But
with a presidential election next year, there will very likely be
another beneficiary: Gov. George W. Bush, who at the moment is the
Republicans' best hope for taking control of the White House. By
