this little town southeast of Charleston about every 90 years or
so, not counting the fire truck that rolled into the Kanawha River
a few summers ago because someone forgot to set the emergency
brake. Now along comes Wesley B. Nugent, a freshly minted graduate
of West Virginia University who wants to be mayor of Pratt, a
sleepy little town where two-thirds of the 680 residents, the
incumbent mayor among them, are senior citizens. By Michael
Janofsky.
