<HEADLINE>
D-BACKS PROMOTE KIM TO BIG LEAGUE  
 TIME IS RIGHT FOR PITCHING PHENOM 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By PEDRO GOMEZ  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Diamondbacks have decided there is no time like the present
for their minor league phenom, pitcher Byung-Hyun Kim.
</P>
<P>
   With little else to prove in the farm system, Kim, who received
a $2.25 million bonus when he signed in March, was promoted to the
major league club Thursday and joined the players at their team
hotel in midtown Manhattan in time for a late dinner.
</P>
<P>
   ``Obviously, people are getting increasingly anxious to see
Kim,'' said General Manager Joe Garagiola Jr., who acknowledged he
was one of those people. ``If the events show he's not ready, he'll
go back.
</P>
<P>
   ``But I don't think that's going to happen. If there is a risk
to be run, this is a pretty good guy to run it with.''
</P>
<P>
   Kim (pronounced Bee-young Hee-yon Kim) had a combined 2.33 ERA
in 38 innings at Double-A El Paso and Triple-A Tucson. He had 53
strikeouts and had walked just 16 batters. More amazingly, opposing
hitters were batting just .150 against Kim.
</P>
<P>
   The submarine-style right-hander, who was starting for the
Sidewinders in Tucson, will be placed in the Diamondbacks' bullpen.
Garagiola said it was unlikely Kim would be thrown into the frying
pan of a close game right away.
</P>
<P>
   ``I would be surprised if his first few outings were in that
type of situation,'' Garagiola said. ``I think Buck (Showalter)
will try to pick a spot to maximize his chance for success.''
</P>
<P>
   At some point, though, Kim will probably get a shot at closing
games for the Diamondbacks. Current closer Gregg Olson has blown
five of his 10 save opportunities.
</P>
<P>
   To make room for Kim, the Diamondbacks optioned reliever Bobby
Chouinard to Tucson.
</P>
<P>
   ``The guy is overmatching these Triple-A guys,'' Garagiola said
of Kim. ``Do we keep sending him out to do what he has been doing,
so we can remind ourselves of how well he looks or bring him up to
see what he can do?
</P>
<P>
   ``Ultimately, everything being done at the minor league level is
for the benefit of the major league club. We felt it was time.'' &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-05-28-99 0220EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
