<TEXT>
<P>
   SOFIA _ Unlike several of its neighbors, Bulgaria has been
surprisingly unshy about backing NATO in the war for Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
   Ivan Kostov, its center-right prime minister, has let NATO
aircraft fly through a large part of Bulgaria's airspace.
</P>
<P>
   Turkish F-16 fighters, which Greece has refused to allow over
the Aegean, can fly across Bulgaria to attack targets in Yugoslavia
from the east. This, say NATO's planners, weakens Serbia's air
