<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    ALBANIA AT-A-GLANCE
 &HT;    With KOSOVO-ALBANIA-$ADV30.
 &HT;    For Use Sun., May 30 And Thereafter.
 &HT;    By BERT ROUGHTON JR. 
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service 
<TEXT>
<P>
   ALBANIA
</P>
<P>
   Capital: Tirana
</P>
<P>
   Government: Fledgling federal democracy.
</P>
<P>
   President: Rexhep Meidani
</P>
<P>
   Prime Minister: Pandeli Majko
</P>
<P>
   Population: 3.5 million (not including 450,000 Kosovar
refugees).
</P>
<P>
   Area: 11,000 square miles (slightly larger than Maryland).
</P>
<P>
   Border Countries: Greece, Macedonia, Yugoslavia (Kosovo and
Montenegro). Italy is 60 miles across the Adriatic Sea.
</P>
<P>
   Climate: Mild temperate; cool, cloudy, wet winters; hot, clear,
dry summers.
</P>
<P>
   Terrain: Mostly mountains and hills; small plains along coast.
About 80 percent of the land is unsuitable for agriculture.
</P>
<P>
   Natural resources: petroleum, natural gas, coal, chromium,
copper, timber and nickel.
</P>
<P>
   Ethnic divisions: Albanian, 95 percent; Greek, 3 percent; Other,
2 percent.
</P>
<P>
   Religions: Muslim, 70 percent; Eastern Orthodox, 20 percent;
Roman Catholic. 10 percent. (All mosques and churches were closed
in 1967 and religious observances prohibited;
</P>
<P>
   Right to practice religion restored in 1990.)
</P>
<P>
   ENDIT
</P>
