<P>
   SUMMER-SPIRITUALITY _ The long, hot summer stretches ahead, a
perfect time to stay cool and find a sense of spirituality. More
then ever, there are books, movies, workshops, retreats and CDs
that offer meaning, and spiritual connection. We offer a guide,
focusing on the latest offerings and a few classics. (Blake,
Atlanta Journal-Consitution). WITH PHOTOS. FOR SATURDAY
</P>
<P>
   LIFESTYLE
</P>
<P>
   WARNER-ON-WOOD _ (Warner, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED
FOR SATURDAY.
</P>
<P>
   SCIENCE/MEDICINE
</P>
<P>
   SKIN-PROTECTION _ WACO, Texas _ Soaking up the hot rays of the
summer sun without protection is like giving skin cancer an open
invitation to form on your skin. ``People are still thinking a tan
is beautiful and the sun and tanning beds are safe,'' said Dr.
James Mason, a dermatologist. ``I think older people are getting
the picture when they see the bumps and skin spots come up, but
younger people feel like they're immune to these types of problems
and don't think about it until it's too late.'' (Mays, Waco
Tribune-Herald) MOVED FOR SATURDAY.
</P>
<P>
   FITNESS-KYUDO _ Meditative Japanese archery is the latest thing
to hit the fitness scene. Talking to members of Austin Kyudo group.
It's more meditation than sport, more like tai chi and yoga than
regular archery. It's not about hitting the target, it's about
discovering more about yourself (how Austin.) (Santos, Austin
American-Statesman). 25. WITH PHOTOS. FOR SATURDAY
</P>
<P>
   ENTERTAINMENT-ARTS
</P>
<P>
   ARTS-CONVENTION _ ATLANTA _ Advancing the Americans for the Arts
convention which comes to Atlanta on Wednesday, 6/3. The group puts
big-business muscle behind the arts and has, in the past, helped
fuel a national dialogue on arts issues. Local participants include
Harriett Sanford, Michael Hightower and Coke executives. (Hulbert
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 25. FOR SUNDAY
</P>
<P>
   CONDUCTOR-SEARCH _ ATLANTA _ A look at the status of the Atlanta
Symphony's search for a new conductor. Who's still on the list of
candidates? Who has dropped off? What kind of talent is the ASO
looking at (rising star, not as expensive as Yoel Levi.) Who is the
ASO competing with for talent? What do insiders around the country
think of the way they're running their search? (Green, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). FOR SUNDAY
</P>
