American-Statesman). 25. WITH PHOTOS. FOR SATURDAY
</P>
<P>
   ENTERTAINMENT-ARTS
</P>
<P>
   ARTS-CONVENTION _ ATLANTA _ Advancing the Americans for the Arts
convention which comes to Atlanta on Wednesday, 6/3. The group puts
big-business muscle behind the arts and has, in the past, helped
fuel a national dialogue on arts issues. Local participants include
Harriett Sanford, Michael Hightower and Coke executives. (Hulbert
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 25. FOR SUNDAY
</P>
<P>
   CONDUCTOR-SEARCH _ ATLANTA _ A look at the status of the Atlanta
Symphony's search for a new conductor. Who's still on the list of
candidates? Who has dropped off? What kind of talent is the ASO
looking at (rising star, not as expensive as Yoel Levi.) Who is the
ASO competing with for talent? What do insiders around the country
think of the way they're running their search? (Green, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). FOR SUNDAY
</P>
