   &UR; KOSOVO &LR;  (``i'' code)
</P>
<P>
   The New York Times plans 4{ pages of stories on the continuing
Kosovo crisis, including two pages for KOSOVO-RECONSTRUCT, a
special report listed below.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-RECONSTRUCT (Undated) _ Special Report: A reconstruction
of the early days of the Yugoslav operation in Kosovo, based on
interviews with scores of refugees, and with senior officials in
Washington and NATO, as well as a computer analysis of reported
horrors from many sources, showing that it was meticulously
organized and aimed, from the outset, at expelling huge numbers of
people. By John Kifner. (4500 words)
</P>
<P>
   We will move this article in both full-length and abridged
versions.
</P>
<P>
   With photos and graphics.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-BELGRADE (Belgrade) _ The Russian envoy, Viktor
Chernomyrdin, arrives for talks with Slobodon Milosevic, the
Yugoslav president, and sounds pessimistic. By Steven Erlanger.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-NATO (Brussels) _ Developments from NATO headquarters;
Strobe Talbott, the deputy secretary of state, is here for talks.
By Roger Cohen.
</P>
