   &UR; OTHER INTERNATIONAL &LR;
</P>
<P>
   INDIA-PAKISTAN (New Delhi) _ Tensions grow in Kashmir as
Pakistan shoots down an Indian helicopter. By Celia W. Dugger.
</P>
<P>
   With map.
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-CABINET (Moscow) _ The deputy prime minister in charge of
the economy, Mikhail Zadornov, resigned on Friday less than a week
after his appointment, plunging the government into new turmoil.
Among other things, he was unhappy that he was not allowed to keep
his portfolio as finance minister. By Michael Wines.
</P>
<P>
   NIGERIA-INAUG (Abuja) _ On Saturday Nigeria returns to civilian
rule as the new president, Olusegun Obasanjo, is sworn in. By
Norimitsu Onishi.
</P>
<P>
   TURKEY-POLITICS (Istanbul) _ The Turkish premier-designate,
Bulent Ecevit, said he had reached agreement with nationalists and
conservatives to form a majority government widely expected to push
key economic reforms. The coalition seems likely to please
financial markets and the powerful military, both of which have had
cause for concern over the last four years with the collapse of
five governments. By Stephen Kinzer.
</P>
