   TULEH-FASHION (New York) _ Josh Patner and Bryan Bradley, the
designers behind Tuleh, who are up for an American Fashion
Designers Award June 2, settle into an outdoor cafe table on
Madison, and watch the fashion parade. By Elizabeth Hayt. Photo.
</P>
<P>
   NITEOUT-FLYER (New York) _ Surveying the crowd last Thursday
night at Stylus, a weekly party held at a Lower East Side sushi
lounge called Never, Hosi Simon, 24, nodded approvingly that few
people were eating. ``If people were eating and ignoring the music,
that would be a bad sign,'' said Simon. He is the editor in chief
of Flyer, a palm-size monthly club listing guide that has become
the equivalent of Zagat's for the deejay set. Riding around the
city on his mountain bike, Simon is an obsessional inspector,
visiting as many as eight clubs a night. By Julie Chaplin. Photo.
</P>
