   TENNIS
</P>
<P>
   TEN-ROSTERS _ Something was missing when two southern schools,
Georgia and Baylor, played in the quarterfinals of the NCAA Tennis
Championships. Where were the Bubbas? On court one, Baylor's Johann
Jooste of South Africa took on Georgia's Hisham Hemeda of Egypt. On
court two, Baylor's Pawel Gajdzik of Poland played Georgia's Talito
Corrales of Spain. Baylor also had Johannes Michalsky of Germany ,
Fanda Stejskal of Prague, Csongor Bibza of Hungary and Frederic
Blaise of France in the wings. Of the 10 players on the Bears'
roster, only Jorge Aldrete of San Diego was born in this country.
Coaches say about 65-70 percent of Division I male college tennis
players are foreign. (Arey, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
