   Artist: John Tesh
</P>
<P>
   Title: ``One World''
</P>
<P>
   Release: May
</P>
<P>
   The buzz: Love him or hate him, Tesh's persistent touring and
concert videos are winning more fans _ even with his new goatee.
</P>
<P>
   Artist: Michael Whalen
</P>
<P>
   Title: ``The Softest Touch''
</P>
<P>
   Release: May
</P>
<P>
   The buzz: A fast-rising New Age composer who has made a name
composing rich, moody instrumental music. Whalen now tackles his
first love _ acoustic piano.
</P>
<P>
   BOOKS
</P>
<P>
   Title: ``Veggie Tales'' series
</P>
<P>
   Author: Phil Vischer
</P>
<P>
   Publisher: Tommy Nelson
</P>
<P>
   At a glance: Bob the Tomato and Larry the Cucumber tell cute
parables with a Christian message.
</P>
<P>
   Title: ``The Visitation''
</P>
<P>
   Author: Frank Peretti
</P>
<P>
   Publisher: Thomas Nelson
</P>
<P>
   At a glance: Before Armageddon was hot and Y2K was unheard of,
Peretti's novels, featuring wars between angels and demons in
contemporary America, sold millions.
</P>
<P>
   Title: ``Sacred Roads''
</P>
<P>
   Author: Nicholas Shrady
</P>
<P>
   Publisher: HarperSanFrancisco
</P>
<P>
   At a glance: Shrady travels to sacred sites around the world. In
India he bathes in the Ganges; in Turkey, he visits the tomb of the
Sufi poet Rumi; in Jerusalem, he worships at the Church of the Holy
Sepulcher.
</P>
<P>
   Title: ``Every Dead Thing''
</P>
<P>
   Author: John Connolly
</P>
<P>
   Publisher: Simon &AMP; Schuster
</P>
<P>
   At a glance: New Age magazine characterizes this thriller as the
``Silence of the Lambs'' gone clairvoyant.
</P>
<P>
   Title: ``Yesterday, I Cried''
</P>
<P>
   Author: Iyanla Vanzant
</P>
<P>
   Publisher: Simon &AMP; Schuster
</P>
<P>
   At a glance: Yesterday she may have been crying, but now Vanzant
is sporting a smile _ all the way to the bank. Vanzant, a former
welfare mother and battered spouse, is one of the New Age
movement's top authors.
</P>
