<SLUG> BC-CORRECTIVE-SMITH-BOS </SLUG>
  
 (Eds.: Newspapers that used the Boston Globe story SMITH-BLACKS (a)
by Kate Zernike, which moved May 17, will wish to use the following
corrective.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Because of incorrect information provided to the Globe, a story
about black Smith College grauates said there were no black
professors at the college in 1970. According to college archives
there were in fact three black professors. The story also gave the
impression black students lived in only three dormitories on
campus. They lived in more than three.
</P>
