<P>
   &UR; CONFLICT IN THE BALKANS &LR;   &UR; (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   YUGOSLAVIA (Budapest) _ Yugoslavia briefly seizes six NATO
soldiers over the border in Bosnia in the latest incursion of
neighboring states. By Kevin Cullen and Susan Milligan. 1200 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   NIGERIA-POWER (Johannesburg) _ Nigeria inaugurates its first
elected president in two decades Saturday amid cautious hopes that
Africa's most populous nation will finally break its long cycle of
corruption, military repression and decay. By Kurt Shillinger. 1000
words.
</P>
<P>
   CHINA-SCHOOLS (Beijing) _ While hundreds of Chinese students
were hurling rocks at the US embassy after the Belgrade bombing,
