   &QL; 
 &UR; VIRUS29 &LR;  _ Computer security experts yesterday said they have
uncovered a Trojan Horse program disguised as spam that allows
hackers to purloin or destroy the files of its victims from
anywhere on the Internet. The BackDoor-G program arrives in e-mail
as a screen saver or PC game update that, when downloaded, exposes
a user's PC to remote Net connections. It is also virtually
undetectable to users. By Jon Swartz
