ADOPT (Douglas, Ariz.) - While Douglas lawyer Mario Reyes was
carrying on with his illegal adoption ring of Mexican babies for
parents in New York City area, he also was devoutly attending
Immaculate Conception Catholic Church in Douglas on a regular
basis, having breakfast each morning with the padre and being made
a lector in the church. The church disowned him, though, after he
was indicted in Mexico for child trafficking last October. He never
went back to his law office in Agua Prieta after that. He took a
job substitute teaching inBisbee, Ariz. Was he also trafficking in
human organs, as isthe word on the street in Douglas? By MARK
SHAFFER. Story will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
