<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR SATURDAY, MAY 29
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Saturday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-CALIF-PICKERS-UNION-NYT (moved on Thursday, May 27)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Thursday, May 27,
about efforts by the United Farm Workers of America to unionize
strawberry workers in California misstated the value of the
nation's annual strawberry crop. It is $600 million, not $600
billion.
</P>
<P>
   BC-TRADING-HOURS-MEDIA-NYT (moved on Thursday, May 27)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Thursday, May 27,
about the reaction of newspapers and television networks to the
Nasdaq decision to add an evening trading session misspelled the
name of the executive vice president of CNNfn. He is David Bohrman,
not Borman.
</P>
<P>
   BC-NAYA-AD-COLUMN-NYT (moved on Wednesday, May 26)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, May 26,
about the distribution of Naya Inc.'s bottled water, referred
incorrectly to the distribution system of another company, Triarc,
which owns Snapple and RC Cola. Most Triarc beverages are delivered
directly, not through brokers.
</P>
