<DOCNO> NYT19990528.0391 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-28 21:49 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A5637 &Cx1f; ttf-z
u l &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-NYLITE(SMILE)-2TAKES-     05-28 0985
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-NYLITE(SMILE)-2TAKES-NYT </SLUG>
  
 May 28, 1999  
(These items may be published) 
(jt) 
 c .1999 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; FOR THOSE WHO TAKE LIFE TOO SERIOUSLY &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Save the whales. Collect the whole set.
</P>
<P>
   A day without sunshine is like, night.
</P>
<P>
   On the other hand, you have different fingers.
</P>
<P>
   I just got lost in thought. It was unfamiliar territory.
</P>
<P>
   42.7 percent of all statistics are made up on the spot.
</P>
<P>
   99 percent of lawyers give the rest a bad name.
</P>
<P>
   I feel like I'm diagonally parked in a parallel universe.
</P>
<P>
   You have the right to remain silent. Anything you say will be
misquoted,
</P>
<P>
   then used against you.
</P>
<P>
   I wonder how much deeper the ocean would be without sponges.
</P>
<P>
   Honk if you love peace and quiet.
</P>
