<P>
   &UR; FOR SUNDAY, MAY 30 &LR;
</P>
<P>
   The New York Times News Service will send the following Money
and Business articles for release Sunday, May 30, 1999:
</P>
<P>
   ELIMINATE: BIZ-FOR-ME, TRUCKS-GM-CHEVY and TRUCKS-LOYALTY.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ON THE SECTION FRONT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   TISCH-LOEWS (New York) _ A generational changing of the guard in
the Tisch family, which runs Loews Corp., doesn't mean the
conglomerate will be any less contrary and cantankerous. By Hilary
Rosenberg. (Moved).
</P>
<P>
   With Graphic.
</P>
<P>
   BANKERS-TRUST (Undated) _ The behind-the-scenes story of Bankers
Trust's misuse of unclaimed customer funds. By Timothy L. O'Brien.
(Moved).
</P>
<P>
   With Graphic.
</P>
<P>
   MARKET-WATCH (New York) _ A weekly feature looking at
developments of the market worldwide. By Gretchen Morgenson.
(Moved).
</P>
<P>
   With Graphic.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INSIDE THE SECTION &LR;
</P>
<P>
   BIZ-PROFILE-FRAGA (Rio de Janeiro, Brazil) _ Profile of Arminio
Fraga, the ex-Wall Streeter who now runs Brazil's central bank,
much to Wall Street's satisfaction. By Simon Romero. (Moved).
</P>
<P>
   With Photo.
</P>
<P>
   BIZ-BRIEFS (Undated) _ A weekly column of short items on people
and personalities that make business more than a dollars and cents
proposition. (Moved).
</P>
<P>
   BIZ-CITIES-TECH (Undated) _ Cities and states everywhere want
their own Silicon whatever, and are prepared to spend some tax
money to foster it. By Michael Brick. (Moved). Photo.
</P>
<P>
   BIZ-ECON-COLUMN (Washington) _ The Economic View column: A look
at Alan Greenspan, chairman of the Federal Reserve. By Richard W.
Stevenson. (Moved).
</P>
<P>
   BIZ-WORLD-BAKU (Undated) _ Charlie Schroeder is the real-life
Rick Blaine of Baku, the gritty oilpatch capital of Azerbaijan. The
expatriates all come in sooner or later to eat and drink and shoot
pool and swap news, and they all know Charlie. So do the country's
none too upright customs agents. By Stephen Kinzer. (Moved).
</P>
<P>
   BIZ-5-QUESTIONS (Undated) _ We hear from the prosecutor who
brought the antitrust case against Toys 'R' Us and the toymakers,
about where enforcement is going in the notoriously manipulated toy
business. By Dana Canedy. (Moved).
</P>
<P>
   With Photo.
</P>
<P>
   BIZ-DIARY (Undated) _ Short items on surveys, research and new
consumer products. (Moved).
</P>
<P>
   INVEST-GM-DELPHI (Troy, Mich.) _ Delphi, the auto parts company
spun-off from General Motors, is distributing shares to GM holders.
Should they hang onto them? By Robyn Meredith. (Moved).
</P>
<P>
   With Graphic and Photo.
</P>
<P>
   INVEST-COLUMN (Undated) _ The investing strategy column: Many
strategies that look good on paper have onlyh been back-tested, and
very few are as successful in the real world. By Mark Hulbert.
(Moved).
</P>
<P>
   With Graphic.
</P>
<P>
   INVEST-INSIGHT-Q&AMP;A (Undated) _ A Q&AMP;A with a market insider. By
Kenneth N. Gilpin. (Moved).
</P>
<P>
   With Photo.
</P>
<P>
   INVEST-DIARY (Undated) _ Investing digest, with Funds Watch and
markets this week. (Moved).
